
** Install additional Packages

  - edit /etc/apt/sources.list

  - afterwards "apt-get update" needs to be called

  - ssh, cvs, rcs, make, gcc


** Search Packages

  - apt-cache search <string>
  - aptitude  search <string>

** Emacs
  - apt-get install ...

    - build-essential
    - texinfo
    - libx11-dev
    - libgtk2.0-dev
    - libxpm-dev
    - libjpeg62-dev
    - libtiff4-dev
    - libungif4-dev
    - libpng-dev
    - libncurses-dev

    - libxt-dev
    - libxaw-headers

    - imagemagick
    - perl-doc

  - Make sure that the --x-includes and the --x-libraries are pointing
    to the right directories. E.g.

  - --x-includes=/usr/include/X11
  - --x-libraries=/usr/lib

** Other Programs

  - ncftp

** X11

  - Use ~/.Xresources

** Access to User

  - sudo passwd root
  - sudo passwd oracle

** Oracle Reinstall

  - apt-get install libaio-dev

  - reinstall the package with the --force-all option. This will
    reinstall the seed database.

  - dpkg --force-all -i oracle-xe-universal-*.deb
  - afterwards call config/script/XE.sh

** IMPOS

  - libxt-dev


** SSH

  - sudo apt-get install ssh
or
  - sudo apt-get install openssh-server

** Firewall

  - sudo ufw status

